---
// The static "lesson" panel showcased in the hero. Content from
// src/content/lessons/build-an-expression-evaluator/03-evaluating-the-ast/lesson-14.md
// (Given/When, the "2 + 3 * 4" -> 14 result, and the checkpoint are the lesson's
// own). For an at-a-glance, no-wrap showcase: the Then is shortened to "the result
// is 14", and the code hint is condensed from the lesson's `case *Bin:` evaluator
// (error handling and the - / cases omitted). Highlighting is applied by hand.
---

<div
	class="overflow-hidden rounded-card border border-white/10 bg-surface shadow-[0_1px_0_rgba(255,255,255,.02),0_30px_60px_-30px_rgba(0,0,0,.5)]"
>
	<!-- window chrome -->
	<div class="flex items-center gap-3 border-b border-white/10 bg-surface-2 px-4 py-3">
		<div class="flex gap-[7px]">
			<span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#3a3d44]"></span>
			<span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#3a3d44]"></span>
			<span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full bg-[#3a3d44]"></span>
		</div>
		<span class="font-mono text-xs text-faint">build-an-expression-evaluator / lesson-14.md</span>
	</div>

	<div class="px-[30px] pt-[26px] pb-7">
		<div class="mb-[9px] font-mono text-[11.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-accent">
			Lesson 14 · Evaluating the AST
		</div>
		<h3 class="mb-[22px] font-display text-[25px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-fg">
			Evaluating the four operators
		</h3>

		<!-- the spec -->
		<div class="mb-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.13em] text-faint">The spec</div>
		<div class="mb-5 rounded-[10px] border border-white/[0.06] border-l-2 border-l-accent bg-well px-4 py-[13px]">
			<div class="mb-[9px] font-mono text-[11.5px] text-faint">
				Scenario: <span class="text-code-soft">Arithmetic evaluates through the tree</span>
			</div>
			<div class="font-mono text-xs leading-[1.7] text-code-soft">
				<div><span class="text-code-blue">Given</span> the expression string "2 + 3 * 4"</div>
				<div><span class="text-code-num">When</span> it is evaluated with EvalString</div>
				<div><span class="text-code-cyan">Then</span> the result is 14</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- your code -->
		<div class="mb-[9px] font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.13em] text-faint">Your code</div>
		<div class="mb-5 overflow-auto rounded-[10px] border border-white/[0.06] bg-well px-4 py-[14px]">
			<pre class="m-0 font-mono text-xs leading-[1.65] text-code-fg"><span class="text-code-comment">// evaluate both sides, then the operator</span>
l, r := Eval(n.Left), Eval(n.Right)
<span class="text-code-blue">switch</span> n.Op &#123;
<span class="text-code-blue">case</span> <span class="text-code-num">"+"</span>: <span class="text-code-blue">return</span> l + r
<span class="text-code-blue">case</span> <span class="text-code-num">"*"</span>: <span class="text-code-blue">return</span> l * r
&#125;<span class="ml-0.5 inline-block h-[15px] w-2 translate-y-[2px] animate-[blink_1.1s_step-end_infinite] bg-code-fg align-[-2px]"></span></pre>
		</div>

		<!-- further reading -->
		<div class="mb-[7px] font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.13em] text-faint">Further Reading</div>
		<p class="mb-5 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-muted">
			Crafting Interpreters, by Robert Nystrom.
		</p>

		<!-- checkpoint -->
		<div class="flex items-center gap-[11px] rounded-[10px] border border-check/30 bg-check/10 px-[15px] py-[13px]">
			<span
				class="flex h-5 w-5 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border-[1.5px] border-check"
			>
				<svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
					<path
						d="M2.5 6.2 5 8.5 9.5 3.5"
						stroke="#6FB894"
						stroke-width="1.6"
						stroke-linecap="round"
						stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
				</svg>
			</span>
			<div>
				<span class="font-display text-[13.5px] font-semibold text-fg">Checkpoint</span>
				<div class="mt-0.5 text-[12.5px] text-dim">
					The evaluator computes all four operators. Commit and stop here.
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
